[{"c":"<p>I stand amazed in the presence</p><p>of Jesus the Nazarene,</p><p>and wonder how He could love me,</p><p>a sinner, condemned, unclean.</p>"},{"c":"<p>How marvelous! How wonderful!</p><p>And my song shall ever be:</p><p>How marvelous! How wonderful</p><p>is my Savior's love for me!</p>"},{"c":"<p>For me it was in the garden</p><p>He prayed: \"Not My will, but Thine.\"</p><p>He had no tears for His own griefs,</p><p>but sweat-drops of blood for mine.</p>"},{"c":"<p>In pity angels beheld Him,</p><p>and came from the world of light</p><p>to comfort Him in the sorrows</p><p>He bore for my soul that night.</p>"},{"c":"<p>He took my sins and my sorrows,</p><p>He made them His very own;</p><p>He bore the burden to Calvary,</p><p>and suffered and died alone.</p>"},{"c":"<p>When with the ransomed in glory</p><p>His face I at last shall see,</p><p>'twill be my joy through the ages</p><p>to sing of His love for me.</p>"}]